                            <p class="- topic/shortdesc shortdesc" css:display="block" css:margin-bottom="0.5em" css:margin-left="0" css:margin-right="0" css:margin-top="0.5em">The NextGen Trading Card Game (NXTCG)
                                features exclusive collectible cards inspired by the Rocket Software
                                NextGen Academy and its Rocketeers. The platform empowers users to
                                buy and sell new cards and related products, creating a dynamic
                                marketplace for fans and collectors.</p>
                            <p class="- topic/p p" css:display="block" css:margin-bottom="0.5em" css:margin-left="0" css:margin-right="0" css:margin-top="1em">ECOMAPP is a Db2 13 for z/OS database for NXTCG. It is compromised
                                of 15 normalized tables with full referential integrity and indexed
                                access paths. Administration is driven by source-controlled DDL and
                                JCL pipelines for build, initialization, statistics, grants, and
                                teardown. </p>
                            <p class="- topic/p p" css:display="block" css:margin-bottom="0.5em" css:margin-left="0" css:margin-right="0" css:margin-top="1em"><strong class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ph b" css:display="inline" css:font-weight="bold">Key Features:</strong></p>
                            <ul class="- topic/ul ul" css:display="block" css:list-style-type="disc" css:margin-bottom="1.33em" css:margin-top="1.33em" css:padding-left="40px" id="ul_fhm_zcd_q3c">
                                <li class="- topic/li li" css:display="list-item">Complete SKU-based
                                    product catalog (4,824 trading card variants)</li>
                                <li class="- topic/li li" css:display="list-item">Multiplier-based
                                    dynamic pricing system</li>
                                <li class="- topic/li li" css:display="list-item">16 normalized
                                    tables with full referential integrity</li>
                                <li class="- topic/li li" css:display="list-item">Performance
                                    indexes on all critical access paths</li>
                                <li class="- topic/li li" css:display="list-item">Split
                                    initialization files for mainframe line length compliance</li>
                                <li class="- topic/li li" css:display="list-item">Automated JCL for
                                    all database operations</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="- topic/p p" css:display="block" css:margin-bottom="0.5em" css:margin-left="0" css:margin-right="0" css:margin-top="1em"><strong class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ph b" css:display="inline" css:font-weight="bold">Product Catalog:</strong></p>
                            <ul class="- topic/ul ul" css:display="block" css:list-style-type="disc" css:margin-bottom="1.33em" css:margin-top="1.33em" css:padding-left="40px" id="ul_ghm_zcd_q3c">
                                <li class="- topic/li li" css:display="list-item">80 Individual
                                    Cards × 60 modifier combinations = 4,800 variants</li>
                                <li class="- topic/li li" css:display="list-item">24 Mystery
                                    Products × 1 variant each = 24 variants</li>
                                <li class="- topic/li li" css:display="list-item">Total: 4,824
                                    sellable SKUs</li>
                            </ul>
